ibbt.sumo.sampleevaluators
Class AbstractSampleQueueManager

java.lang.Object
  ibbt.sumo.sampleevaluators.AbstractSampleQueueManager
Direct Known Subclasses:
DatasetSampleEvaluator, DefaultSampleQueueManager
public abstract class AbstractSampleQueueManager
extends java.lang.Object

This class manages input, output and pending queues for samples that need to be evaluated or have been evaluated. This abstract base class does not implement the input queue, which is covered by the derived class.

public void submitEvaluatedSample(EvaluationUnit unit)
Signal that a set of samples have been evaluated Valid termination states include: EVALUATED: The point was evaluated correctly. AGAIN: The point wasn't evaluated, but might succeed a next time (for cluster failover, reintroduce in new samples queue). FAILED: The point can't be evaluated.
